
@startuml
skinparam classAttributeIconName true

class House {
  -address: String
  -buildingMaterial: String (wood, brick, concrete)
  -hasBasement: Boolean
  -basement: Basement
}

class Basement {
  -name: String
  -size: Double
}

class EarthBasement <|-- Basement
class ConcreteBasement <|-- Basement

EarthBasement {
  -humidityLevel: Double
}

ConcreteBasement {
}

class SemiDetachedHouse <|-- House
SemiDetachedHouse {
  -hasGarden: Boolean
  -numberOfWindows: Integer
  -parking: Parking
}

abstract class Parking {
  -type: String
}

class Carport <|-- Parking
class Garage <|-- Parking

Carport {
  -isDouble: Boolean
  -hasFlatRoof: Boolean
}

Garage {
  -hasAutomaticDoor: Boolean
}

class Company {
  -name: String
  -address: String
}

class JobLog {
  -company: Company
  -house: House
  -hours: Integer
  -agreedPrice: Double
}

House "1" *-- "0..*" Company : serviced by
House "1" *-- "0..1" Basement : has
SemiDetachedHouse "1" -- "1" Parking : has
Company "1" *-- "0..*" JobLog : performs job at
@enduml

---

### Explanation of Key Elements:

- **`House`**: Base class storing address and building material. It may have a `Basement`.
- **`Basement`**: Abstract class with two subclasses: `EarthBasement` and `ConcreteBasement`. Only `EarthBasement` stores humidity.
- **`SemiDetachedHouse`**: A special type of house that extends `House`, with additional attributes like garden, windows, and parking.
- **`Parking`**: Abstract base class for `Carport` and `Garage`, each with their own specific properties.
- **`Company`**: Stores name and address; services multiple houses.
- **`JobLog`**: Records work done by a company on a house, including hours and price.

